Greetings! 

Thank you for contacting EA Tech Support. We are happy to assist you in any issue that you have with our games. Though I do apologize that you are experiencing this issue and let me help you solve it in the best way that I can. 

Be sure that you have installed the game in proper order. The files might get corrupt if you didn't follow the right order of installation. To ensure a proper installation of the Battlefield 2 series, please install in the following order. If you do not have all of the expansion and booster packs please skip and install the next software on the list. 

1. Install Battlefield 2 
Note: If you have the Battlefield 2 Deluxe pack, install and skip to step 3. 
2. Install Battlefield 2: Special Forces. 
3. Install the 1.41 full patch. 
This patch can be found here. 
4. Install Battlefield 2: Armored Fury. 
5. Install Battlefield 2: Euro Force. 
6. Install the 1.41 full patch once again. 

Once this is done you will have the complete installation of the Battlefield 2 series lineup. 

About the command lines, we do thank you for supporting our games and I do apologize for your situation, and the inconvenience that this causes you. Unfortunately, we cannot assist you with gameplay or code questions. Please refer to Battlefield 2 official web site for more information. There are also other resources available for game assistance web sites like www.gamefaqs.com, or other game guides for help, codes, and walkthroughs are a good start. 

If you have any more issues and comments or suggestions, please don't hesitate to contact us again at EA Support or try to search for other solutions at our support site, support.ea.com. Thank you for contacting EA Tech Support
